creator: Task Force Tips LLC
descriptionHtml:
The TFT SHO-FLOW® Bluetooth® water flow meter is designed to quickly determine the flow rate present in a fire hose line and wirelessly transmit the rate to a nearby smart device. In addition to measuring flow rate you will also be able to view total gallons flowed and easily reset that value whenever connected to a SHO-FLOW. Any firefighting, training, or testing operation that utilizes hose lines or nozzles is a potential application for the SHO-FLOW.

This app requires a TFT SHO-FLOW flow meter.

Features:
- Display flowrate in real time through a Bluetooth connection
- Display total gallons flowed in 10 gallon (40 liter) increments
- Easily change flow units from GPM, GPS, LPM, and LPS
- Transmit real time data to remote viewers up to ¼ mile away

Please read manual before operation.

The Bluetooth® word mark and logos are registered trademarks owned by Bluetooth SIG, Inc. and any use of such marks by Task Force Tips, LLC is under license.

title: Sho-Flow

creator: Task Force Tips LLC
descriptionHtml:
The SHO-FLOW app is a dual featured application that can be used with or without a TFT SHO-FLOW® Bluetooth® flow meter. When used in conjunction with a SHO-FLOW, users can determine actual flow rates for fire hose lines and nozzles as well as calculate true Pump Discharge Pressures (PDP), Nozzle Reaction, and Hose Friction. In addition an NFPA 1962 nozzle flow test can be performed. As a stand-alone water flow calculator, many of these functions can be performed using established fire flow formulas. The app also includes water flow education videos and recommendations for target fire flows when using water or foam.
